    <h1>8.1.3.2 Actions</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"id-8.1.3.2Actions-Introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>Actions are defined in the Data Analysis Definition (DAD) as the last st=
ep. They get executed when all previous steps where successful.</p>
<p>You can probably agree that a RASQL statement is not well suited for spe=
cifying the contents of an email or a website notification. This document p=
resents a workable alternative for this.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.3.2Actions-Impactedactiontypes">Impacted action types</h2>
<p>The following action types are impacted by this:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Website notification<br>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">contains a title, body and severity indic=
ator</li>
</ul></li>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">Email notification<br>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">contains a TO recipient, CC recipients, a=
 subject and a body.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.3.2Actions-Howcanthesebedefinedbytheuser">How can these be=
 defined by the user</h2>
<p>A dedicated UI should be defined so a user can easily define them. The u=
ser should also specify a unique key to identify each email/website notific=
ation. These keys should be unique per DAD.</p>
<p>When using the WEBNOTIFICATION or EMAIL actions, the user should specify=
 the key of the template they wish to use.</p>
<p>Inside the body and subject, predefined tokens can be used to specify va=
riable values, such as Temperature etc.</p>
<p>These predefined tokens can only be translated using values that are ava=
ilable in the data analysis definition state.</p>
<p><br></p>
